All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    Authenticator
    Before each request is processed, the authenticator determines whether to cancel the request or now.
    ExchangePacket
    This class is a simplified implementation of HttpExchange.
    This class provides methods to examine requests from the client, and send a response back.
    ExchangePacketProvider
    Service provider class for ExchangePacket.
    FileBytesAdapter
    This interface determines the bytes to save when adding to the FilePreHandler.
    FileNameAdapter
    This interface determines the file name to use when adding to the FilePreHandler.
    FilePostHandler
    A Request Handler that returns a file.
    FilePreHandler
    A Request Handler that returns a file and preloaded bytes.
    HTTPCode
    A list of expected HTTP status codes.
    HttpServer
    This class is a simplified implementation of HttpServer.
    At least one RequestHandler must be created in order to process requests.
    PredicateHandler
    The Request Handler will process each request differently depending on the predicate.
    RedirectHandler
    A Request Handler that redirects to a different URL without saving to the history.
    RequestHandler
    This class is a simplified implementation of HttpHandler.
    A handler used to process HTTP exchanges.
    RequestMethod
    A list of expected HTTP method requests.
    RootHandler
    By default the Http Server will use the most specific context for requests; This means however, creating a Request Handler using context / will process all requests without a handler instead of sending a 404 response.
